{"ts":"2026-06-27T07:01:56.718Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing Interactive Controls**\n\nI am now focusing on the interactive elements, specifically an emulated security warning box at the top, indicating \"Secure Emulation Mode\". I'm planning a filter/search bar with category pills for roles, client enclaves, and statuses. I will use a split layout with a user list table on the left, showing user profiles with quick access controls, and a detailed permission ledger on the right. User selection will dynamically update the ledger, showing security details and action previews.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
