{"ts":"2026-06-27T07:01:58.825Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining User Attributes**\n\nI've been examining the `User` interface. Right now, I'm focused on the attributes, specifically `id`, `name`, `email`, `role`, `clearance`, `status`, and `avatarUrl`. I'm breaking down what each field represents and its type to fully understand the user's data structure. I'm noting the use of a union type for `status`.\n\n\n**Considering Role Implementation**\n\nI'm now diving into role implementation. My focus has shifted to the `Role` interface. I'm noting the definition with specific role names: \"Client\", \"Administrator\", and \"Auditor\". I'm also examining the `permissions` array, and exploring how these roles relate to the broader task of building `/admin/users` as a frontend preview.\n\n\n**Formulating Design Plan**\n\nI'm now formulating the design plan, as requested, beginning with the page narrative. I'm focusing on the user's need to audit and govern user roles and permissions. I will work through each point: Visual metaphor, Layout strategy, Interaction strategy, Mobile strategy, Files to change, and Files not to touch. My aim is to create a polished, enterprise-grade admin UI for `/admin/users`, as required.\n\n\n**Designing Security Interface**\n\nI am now visualizing the security interface, focusing on cryptographic integrity and RBAC. The design will use a key matrix metaphor with permission keycards, structured tags, and isolated client enclaves. I aim to create a high-tech dashboard using SVG badges and a real-time permission visualizer. A clear \"BACKEND & AUTH INTEGRATION PHASE\" notice will be included.\n\n\n**Designing Interactive Controls**\n\nI am now focusing on the interactive elements, specifically an emulated security warning box at the top, indicating \"Secure Emulation Mode\". I'm planning a filter/search bar with category pills for roles, client enclaves, and statuses. I will use a split layout with a user list table on the left, showing user profiles with quick access controls, and a detailed permission ledger on the right. User selection will dynamically update the ledger, showing security details and action previews.\n\n\n**Simulating Interactive Features**\n\nI'm now implementing interactive features, focusing on simulations. Admin actions include email entry, role selection (`client_admin`, etc.), client association, and clearance level setting. A \"Generate Secure Invitation Code\" button will trigger a cryptographic handshake simulation, outputting an invitation preview token. I'm focusing on \"Change Role\", \"Deactivate/Reactivate\", and \"Reset Access\" previews. Hover effects are in progress, using Tailwind for glows.\n\n\n"}}
