{"ts":"2026-06-27T07:02:12.999Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Considering Table Implementations**\n\nI'm evaluating the `DataTable` component. While it's great for general data presentation, I'm concerned about its suitability for specific RBAC actions like \"invite user preview\" or \"change role\" due to its current parameter set. I'm exploring if it needs modification or if other table implementations might be a better fit.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Custom Dashboard**\n\nI've shifted focus to a custom RBAC dashboard. Developing a tailored `/admin/users` page aligns perfectly with our UI quality goals, offering a premium and interactive experience. I can ensure consistency by reusing existing styles and accents. I am in the midst of determining if there are any standard files or mock data to be aware of. I am making sure the mock dataset of users uses the requested roles and can be mapped or converted.\n\n\n**Designing RBAC Dashboard**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in designing the `/admin/users` layout. I'm prioritizing role filters, including client association, status, and permission summaries. The roles are `client_admin`, `client_member`, and `gff_admin`, all essential for our RBAC system. I'm focusing on local-only actions (previews), avoiding actual security implementation for now, and I'll include a clear backend/auth notice. I'm confirming correct Lucide import and icon usage for a secure, polished UI.\n\n\n**Developing UI Metrics**\n\nI'm expanding the `/admin/users` design to include key metric badges at the top, such as total monitored identities, enclave-bound roles, and security status. I'm also finalizing a backend/auth notice box with a premium design featuring cyber elements, a clear warning about the emulated state, and a button to view simulated auth logs. I'm focusing on making it feel secure and interactive.\n\n\n**Constructing Inspector Pane**\n\nI'm now building the interactive workspace layout. I've designed an interactive table on the left with headers for Identity, Role, Enclave, Clearance, Status, and Actions. Clicking a row selects a user, and hovering offers a cyber-neon glow. On the right, I'm developing a Role/Identity Inspector Pane to show details such as token, clearance, email, and ID upon user selection. I'm focusing on the permissions matrix that updates in real time and the local-only security actions panel for role changes and deactivation.\n\n\n"}}
