ctive Role Modifier and Status Toggle for local state manipulation. A button to reset dual-key FIDO2 access is also planned.\n\n\n**Simulating Security Logs**\n\nI'm now detailing the real-time terminal output at the bottom. This will display session-local security logs. I will make sure custom logs append with high-fidelity timestamps whenever an action is performed, such as role change or deactivation. The logs are planned to include events like \"Operator initiated role modification\" and \"Policy authorized transition.\" These logs will be appended in real-time, such as when an invitation is processed.\n\n\n**Refining Invitation Process**\n\nI'm now detailing the \"Generate Secure Invitation Seal\" process, a dropdown for Client Enclave selection, and a dropdown for Initial Clearance. Clicking the CTA button will generate a simulated cryptographic invitation, complete with a loading state, and generates a simulated invitation link. It will also add the user to the local directory with a pending status and print a local notice. The UI is looking incredible. I'll need to double-check the rules in `gff-ai-guardrails` next.\n\n\n**Validating Design Principles**\n\nI'm now evaluating the design principles against my evolving UI mockups, ensuring I meet all requirements and avoid design pitfalls. I'm carefully reviewing the guidelines regarding the landing page, data, and backend to stay compliant. This includes reviewing mockups for mobile-responsiveness and the \"premium, enterprise, Apple-like UI\" style.\n\n\n**Styling Refinement**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on UI aesthetics. My focus is crafting a premium, cohesive design. I'm leveraging deep blacks, subtle dark grey borders, glowing mono text, and refined silver/white typography. I'm focusing on high-precision micro-interactions. I'm exploring specific UI elements to evoke an \"expensive\" feel. Let's make sure it's pixel perfect!\n\n\n**Populating Initial User Data**\n\nI'm now populating the mock user data, definin