{"ts":"2026-06-27T07:13:40.221Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"ab4qqrtv","input":{"summary":"I have built the Admin Users and RBAC management page at `/admin/users` as a secure-looking, premium, and highly interactive frontend-only administration console.\n\n### Key Implementation Details:\n1. **Design Narrative & Metaphor**: Built the UI using a \"Cryptographic Key Matrix\" metaphor. Users are rendered as secured identity cards with distinct clearance tiers, enclaves, and cryptographic permission arrays.\n2. **Robust Frontend-only State**: Included a deterministic list of initial mock users (aligned with the clients in `lib/mock-data-model.ts`) with role permissions (`gff_admin`, `client_admin`, `client_member`).\n3. **Core Local Interactive Actions**:\n   - **Provision Identity (Invite Preview)**: Built an advanced overlay dialog where admins can enter operator details and target roles, view a simulated RSA-4096 envelope seal progress, and copy a generated invitation token. Clicking \"Accept Invitation (Emulated)\" updates the user list immediately.\n   - **Change Role Preview**: Changing roles dynamically updates their capability permissions matrix and clearance level in local state.\n   - **Deactivate/Activate Preview**: Allows admins to revoke or restore credentials, terminating simulated telemetry sessions.\n   - **Reset Credentials Preview**: Simulates a Hardware Security Module (HSM) rollover, outputting FIDO2 recovery tokens.\n4. **Backend/Auth Phase Notice & Diagnostic Stream**: Included an outstanding, code-bracket styled alert highlighting \"Secure Emulation Mode\". The banner includes an interactive \"Verify Vanguard OIDC Handshake\" button that prints real-time federated OIDC handshaking log diagnostics to verify Phase 5 enterprise readiness (e.g. Okta / Azure AD OIDC binding).\n5. **Polished Design & Mobile responsiveness**: Designed matching GFF AI's black-and-silver theme, fully responsive for tablets/mobiles, using Lucide icons.\n6. **Linting & Type Safety Validation**: Verified type-safety using `npx tsc --noEmit` and successfully ran `npx eslint app/admin/users/page.tsx` resulting in 0 errors/warnings. Tested on Darwin. No changes were made to the approved landing page.","verified":true}}}
